				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How can this raid even happen?<a name="36770"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 2:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I learned my lessons about pickup raids back when I was actively hunting Naggy and Vox.
<br />
The first thing I look for is how much bickering is going on?
<br />
Next thing is whether or not there is an established leader of the raid.
<br />
Lastly does this established leader make any bit of sense on his strategy?
<br />

<br />
I have been on a pickup raid for AD and it actually went quite well.  We had a completely full raid and others on the sidelines that wanted the flag.  From the get go there was one person leading the raid and he had a band of cronies to help him with getting the cattle hurded, so to speak<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />
I have also been on a pickup raid for MB in PoI that absolutely sucked.  Luckily on this one I did not suffer the death and dismemberment of the rest of the raid as I went through my checklist and decided not to stick around.
<br />

<br />
Pickup raids are like pickup groups, if everyone is doing what they're supposed to they work out.</span></td>
